title: Doris_M1_Start
tags: mission1 doris greeting
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Doris the Baker — Mission 1 dialogue.
// Author: Inara Vellis (Lead Memory Writer)
// Spec:   Docs/Depth_Bible/Mission_1_2_Focus/01_DORIS_THE_BAKER.md § 7
// Guide:  Docs/GAMEPLAY_GUIDE_MISSION_1.md § 8–10, § 15
//
// Voice signature (Vellis Rules § 2.1):
//   • Bread metaphors for everything.
//   • Does NOT mention Elric by name in M1.
//   • Short sentences (~12 words avg).
//   • Eye contact made, then gently broken.
//   • Offers tea unprompted.
//   • Does not say "goodbye" at end of M1.
//
// Variables wired through YarnVillageStateBridge.cs:
//   $trust_doris (int 0-100)
//   $coin (int)
//   $polish_quality ("Perfect" | "Acceptable" | "Mild")
//   $asked_about_predecessor (bool)
//   $refused_doris_orb (bool)
//   $doris_owes_player (int — negative = you owe Doris)
//   $vow_5_honest_coin (int 0-100)
//   $vow_1_consent (int 0-100)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

<<eyes_look_at "player">>
Doris: You're the new one.
Doris: I thought you'd be taller.
Doris: Don't mind me — I thought that about the old one, too.
<<wait 1.5>>
Doris: Come in. The kettle's only just stopped.

-> "Hello. Are you Doris?"
    Doris: Aye. The very same.
    Doris: They've put my name on the sign and everything. Look — there.
    <<jump Doris_M1_BakeryEnter>>
-> (Nod silently and follow her in)
    Doris: A quiet one, then. Good.
    Doris: The bread likes quiet.
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 1>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_BakeryEnter>>
-> "Who was the old one?"
    Doris: ... Mm.
    Doris: That's a conversation for a longer day.
    Doris: Come in. Tea first.
    <<set $asked_about_predecessor = true>>
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 2>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_BakeryEnter>>

===

title: Doris_M1_BakeryEnter
tags: mission1 doris bakery_interior
---
<<set $met_doris = true>>
<<play_animation "Doris" "wipes_hands_on_apron">>

Doris: Mind the flour.
Doris: I haven't swept since Tuesday. I keep meaning to.
Doris: ... The shop next door is yours. The Hollow.
Doris: I've been keeping the key safe for you.

-> "Thank you."
    Doris: Of course.
-> "Is the shop ready?"
    Doris: It's clean. It's been waited-in. You'll find your way around.

Doris: ... I have something for you. Before you go in.
Doris: I'd like to be your first customer, if that's all right.

-> "I'd like that."
    Doris: Aye. That's why I want to be the first.
    <<jump Doris_M1_OfferOrb>>
-> "I haven't started yet."
    Doris: Aye. That's why I want to be the first.
    Doris: Otherwise you might come in expecting strangers.
    <<jump Doris_M1_OfferOrb>>

===

title: Doris_M1_OfferOrb
tags: mission1 doris offer_orb
---
<<show_orb "DOR-001">>
<<eyes_look_at "orb">>

Doris: This is the memory.
Doris: Hold it like you'd hold a hot bun. Not by the side. Underneath.
<<wait 0.8>>
Doris: It's a small thing.
Doris: First time I made bread that didn't shame me.
Doris: Most days I think of it.
Doris: I want to put it down, now, for a while.
Doris: Will you take it?

-> "I will. What do you want for it?"
    <<jump Doris_M1_PriceNegotiation>>
-> "Tell me more about it first."
    <<jump Doris_M1_AboutTheLoaves>>
-> "I'd rather not, today."
    Doris: Aye. Some days are not the day.
    Doris: I'll be here when one is.
    <<set $refused_doris_orb = true>>
    <<adjust_vow "vow1" 2>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_RefusedPath>>

===

title: Doris_M1_AboutTheLoaves
tags: mission1 doris loaves_aside
---
// The 5-line aside — Mission 1's quiet writing peak.

Doris: I was twenty-four.
Doris: The oven was new. The bricks were new. I was new.
Doris: I'd been baking other people's bread for nine years.
Doris: That morning was the first morning that was just mine.
Doris: I want to take a rest from carrying it. That's all.

<<jump Doris_M1_PriceNegotiation>>

===

title: Doris_M1_PriceNegotiation
tags: mission1 doris price
---
Doris: Four coppers, if you're asking.
Doris: It's a small memory. I'll not have you overpay your first day.

-> "Four coppers is fair." (Honor the price)
    Doris: Aye. Thank you.
    <<adjust_coin -4>>
    <<adjust_vow "vow5" 2>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_HandOff>>
-> "I'll pay six." (Counter-offer high)
    Doris: That's too much. I'll not have you ruin yourself.
    Doris: Take it back. — Well. Take *some* back.
    Doris: Five, then. Final.
    <<adjust_coin -5>>
    <<adjust_vow "vow5" 3>>
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 1>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_HandOff>>
-> "Two coppers. That's all I have." (Underpay)
    Doris: ...
    Doris: Aye, that'll do. Bring the rest when you find some.
    <<adjust_coin -2>>
    <<set $doris_owes_player = -2>>
    <<adjust_vow "vow5" -1>>
    <<jump Doris_M1_HandOff>>

===

title: Doris_M1_HandOff
tags: mission1 doris hand_off
---
<<play_animation "Doris" "ACS_Offer_Box">>

Doris: There.
Doris: The old keeper showed me how to make it. Took me four tries.
Doris: I cracked the first three. The cat watched me. Judged me, I think.
<<wait 1.0>>
Doris: I'll be in the bakery if you want me. Knock twice.
Doris: There's a kettle on the workbench. Mind the wood stove — it bites.

<<give_player_orb "DOR-001">>
<<unlock_hollow_door>>
<<dialogue_end>>

===

title: Doris_M1_RefusedPath
tags: mission1 doris refused
---
// Player declined her orb. Mission 1 takes the quiet alternate route.
// Per Mission 1 Guide § 9.4 — the cozy contract honours refusal.

Doris: The shop's still yours.
Doris: Go in. Sit a while. The kettle is on.
Doris: I'll be here when you're ready.

<<unlock_hollow_door>>
<<dialogue_end>>

===

title: Doris_M1_AfterPolish_Return
tags: mission1 doris after_polish
---
// Player returns to the bakery after polishing DOR-001.
// Branches on $polish_quality.

<<eyes_look_at "player">>
Doris: Aye.
Doris: There it is. That's the morning.

<<if $polish_quality == "Perfect">>
    Doris: You did it cleaner than I remembered it.
    Doris: I think you'll do.
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 3>>
<<elseif $polish_quality == "Acceptable">>
    Doris: You did it kindly. That's what matters.
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 2>>
<<else>>
    Doris: ... It's the morning still. A little dimmer. But mine.
    Doris: First days are like that. I won't hold it.
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 1>>
<<endif>>

Doris: Sleep tonight. Dreams come.
Doris: I'll see you again, eventually.

<<play_animation "Doris" "return_to_kneading">>
<<dialogue_end>>

===

title: Doris_M2_MorningGreeting
tags: mission2 doris morning_brief
---
// Day 2 morning — optional brief stop at Doris's bakery before Gerrold arrives.
// Per Mission 2 Guide § 7.2.

<<eyes_look_at "player">>
Doris: You slept. Good.
Doris: Tea's on the bench in your shop — drink it while it's warm.

<<if $asked_about_predecessor == true>>
    Doris: ... And the old keeper — Marin — she was a tall one, like I said you weren't.
    Doris: Worked the bench you've been at. Left without a word.
    Doris: We were friends, I think.
    <<adjust_trust "doris" 1>>

    -> "How was she?"
        Doris: Quiet. Took her tea black.
        Doris: Knew every villager's first-name by their first month here.
        Doris: ... I miss her.
        <<jump Doris_M2_MorningGreetingExit>>
    -> "Did she leave a note?"
        Doris: Aye, she left them everywhere.
        Doris: Read the one above your bench.
        <<jump Doris_M2_MorningGreetingExit>>
    -> "Goodbye."
        <<jump Doris_M2_MorningGreetingExit>>
<<else>>
    Doris: Pickle's been on the windowsill since you opened the door yesterday, has she?
    Doris: She does that. She did that with the old keeper, too.
    <<jump Doris_M2_MorningGreetingExit>>
<<endif>>

===

title: Doris_M2_MorningGreetingExit
tags: mission2 doris morning_brief_exit
---
Doris: Off with you. The day's started.

<<play_animation "Doris" "return_to_kneading">>
<<dialogue_end>>

===
